oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: St. Peter's, Rome
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: View of the obelisk in the Piazza San Pietro (St. Peter's Square) and of the Basilica di San Pietro in Vaticano (St. Peter's Basilica).

St. Peter's Basilica is believed to be located on the site of the Circus of Nero and St. Peter's burial place. Current structure built 1505-1615. St. Peter's Square built between 1656 and 1667. Obelisk from 13th century BC in Egypt and moved to Rome in the 1st century.
